abstract = {This paper will present a systematic approach for designing hypermedia environments for online learning. First, I will discuss distance education, online courses, and general considerations for designing online learning environments. Second, I will present a brief history and definition of hypermedia, its attributes, and theoretical background. Third, I will present and discuss a systems approach to developing hypermedia to be used as part of courses and learning environments delivered on the Internet. Issues relating to structuring of the information, branching and interactivity, user interface, and navigation will be discussed in detail. Reprinted by permission of the publisher.},
